import Foundation

// Beginner-facing "HOW TO USE" examples shown in the node palette's detail card
// (NodeSpecCard). Keyed by spec id; nodes without an entry just show their description.
// Style: real node + port names, → for wiring, what you SEE as the payoff.
nonisolated enum NodeUsage {
    static let text: [String: String] = [
        "face-region": "Face Region.mask → Hide.mask → Size: only the pins on your face stay visible. Or mask → Palette.t to paint the face a hot color while the room stays cold.",
        "body-region": "Set REGION = hands, then mask → Multiply.a with Noise.out → Output.z: turbulence erupts only around your hands. REGION = background + mask → Hide hides everything but you.",
        "background": "Add the node and drag R/G/B — the void behind the pins changes instantly. No wires needed.",
        "light": "Add the node, set TYPE = point, drag X/Y and watch the shading move across the cloud. INTENSITY up for drama; wire Hand Position.x → an exposed X to carry the light in your hand.",
        "shape": "Shape.shape → Output.shape turns every pin into that form. Add Spin.rot → Output.rotation to see cubes/diamonds tumble.",
        "shape-by-depth": "Depth.depth → depth, shape → Output.shape: pins near you stay spheres, far pins become the TARGET shape. Swap NEARMORPH/FARMORPH to reverse it.",
        "shape-blend": "Noise.out → amount, shape → Output.shape: the noise field decides where spheres morph into the TARGET shape, per pin.",
        "noise": "Noise.out → Output.z makes the wall boil; out → Size.size makes pins pulse in patches. Pick a MAP and wire color → Output.color for colored noise. Watch the preview in the minimap slot.",
        "counter": "Clock.quarter → count: VALUE climbs 0→1 over WRAP beats then wraps. value → Size.base = a build that resets. On Start.fired → reset restarts it with the patch.",
        "on-start": "seconds → Value Display to watch the patch clock climb from the moment the node lands. seconds → Sine.in gives an ever-evolving wave; fired → Counter.reset zeroes things at launch.",
        "toggle": "Hand Gesture.fist → flip, out → Gate.open: one fist mutes a lane, the next un-mutes. out → Binary Display shows the current state.",
        "timer": "Clock.bar → start: elapsed ramps 0→1 over DURATION each bar — wire elapsed → Displace.amount for a swell that resets. done → the next Timer chains scenes.",
        "gate": "LFO.out → in, Toggle.out → open: the wobble only passes while the toggle is up — mute any modulation on demand.",
        "sample-hold": "LFO.out → in, Clock.quarter → trigger: smooth wobble becomes stepped jumps locked to the beat. out → Palette.shift for beat-locked color moves.",
        "step-sequencer": "Clock.eighth → step, value → Size.base: an 8-step size groove. Draw the pattern with the S1–S8 sliders; stepIndex → Palette.t cycles color per step.",
        "clock": "The patch metronome: quarter/eighth/bar fire on the global BPM. quarter → Envelope.trigger → Size.size = the classic beat pulse.",
        "envelope": "Clock.quarter → trigger, out → Size.size: each beat swells and falls (ATTACK/RELEASE shape it). Also great into Displace.amount.",
        "hand-position": "x → an exposed Palette.shift and colors follow your hand across the frame; y → Camera orbit for a head-tracked stage. SMOOTHING calms jitter.",
        "hand-gesture": "palm/fist/peace/point stay HIGH while held. fist → Toggle.flip latches states; point → Shockwave.fire throws rings on a point.",
        "person-present": "entered → Shockwave.fire greets whoever walks in with a ring; present → Gate.open only lets effects run while someone is in frame.",
        "depth": "The heart node — sensor AND cloud: position/z → Output is the spine of every patch (METRIC = real-intrinsics TDLidar cloud, FREE = intrinsic-free fan). Fan depth out too: depth → Palette.t colors by distance, depth → Shape by Depth.depth morphs by distance.",
        "pinout": "Pin-art with real 3D depth: Depth.position → position, Depth.z → z, both outs → Output. Points lock to the home grid and extend by true metric depth. MORPH 0→1 melts the grid back into the cloud — drive it with an LFO for grid↔cloud breathing.",
        "palette": "Any 0-1 field → t becomes color: Depth.depth → t = thermal camera look. SHIFT slides the map; drive t with Noise.out for animated color fields.",
        "lfo": "The free-running modulator: out → Size.size (breathing), out → an exposed Twist.angle (swaying), RATE at 8 with SQUARE = strobe.",
        "random": "A frozen per-pin random 0-1: out → Size.size gives every pin its own size; out → Palette.t confetti-colors the wall. Reseed with SEED.",
        "shockwave": "Fires expanding rings: Beat Trigger.low → fire (or tap the viewport). pulse → Output.z kicks the wall outward; pulse → Size.size makes rings of giant pins.",
        "freeze": "Wire a field through it and raise HOLD to 1: the field statues mid-motion, release melts back to live. The freeze pad drives this node.",
        "value-display": "The multimeter: wire anything → in and read the live number on the card. First stop when a patch 'does nothing' — check the signal is actually moving.",
        "binary-display": "YES/NO readout for triggers and gates: Hand Gesture.fist → in confirms the gesture actually fires before you wire it into the patch.",

        // ---- generated from the registry audit (verified port names) ----
        "abs": "Subtract.out → in; out → Size.size sizes pins by how far two fields differ, always positive.",
        "add": "Wave.height → a, Ripple.height → b; out → Output.z stacks two motions on the wall — the standard way to sum surfaces.",
        "audio-levels": "No inputs; bass → Size.size makes the cloud thump with the kick (allow mic access — the mic starts the moment the node exists). mid/high/rms too.",
        "audio-rms": "rms → Shape Morph.blend morphs spheres → cubes with overall loudness — currently identical to Audio Levels.rms.",
        "beat-trigger": "low → Envelope.trigger, Envelope.out → Strobe Color.flash: kick drums flash the cloud. mid/high catch snares and hats.",
        "bloom": "Add it and raise INTENSITY: bright pins halo. Pair with Palette's hot ends, Strobe Color flashes, or Render Settings GHOST for full hologram glow.",
        "brightness": "Video Color.color → color, out → Output.color; GAIN 2 doubles the feed, LIFT raises the black floor — quick exposure trim before Output.",
        "burst": "burst → Strobe Color.flash — sudden loud hits (claps, stabs) pop the cloud white for a few frames.",
        "camera": "No wires — the renderer reads the Camera node directly (any Camera, not just the default). Raise PARALLAX + DEPTH PUSH and jog ORBIT X/Y to turntable the cloud in 3D.",
        "chance": "Clock.quarter → trigger, PROBABILITY 0.5; out → Envelope.trigger fires the swell on a random half of the beats.",
        "clamp": "Noise.out → in, MIN 0 MAX 1; out → Output.z stops spikes punching through the camera — the seatbelt before any output.",
        "color-clamp": "Palette.color → color, out → Output.color; LOW 0.2 crushes blacks up to grey, HIGH 0.8 clips highlights flat.",
        "color-gamma": "Video Color.color → color, out → Output.color; GAMMA 0.5 lifts shadow detail, 2 sinks it into black.",
        "color-invert": "Video Color.color → color, out → Output.color for a live negative; AMOUNT 0.5 sits halfway between original and inverse.",
        "color-levels": "Video Color.color → color, out → Output.color; one node for the full tone chain — GAMMA curve first, then GAIN multiply and LIFT add.",
        "color-mix": "Palette.color → a, Video Color.color → b, Depth.depth → t, out → Output.color: far pins show the palette, near pins the camera feed.",
        "color-screen": "Palette.color → a, Video Color.color → b, out → Output.color: screen-blends the two layers — only ever brightens, like stacked projectors.",
        "comment": "Type straight on the card while it's selected (or in the NOTE field below). Park one beside a cluster to explain a patch — the Device Test template uses them as a checklist.",
        "compare": "Depth.depth → a, Constant.out (VALUE 0.5) → b; aGreater → Hide.mask shows only pins nearer than the cutoff.",
        "constant": "No inputs; out → Size.size with VALUE 2 doubles every pin, or wire it into any exposed param port as a fixed setting.",
        "contrast": "Video Color.color → color, out → Output.color; AMOUNT 2 crunches the feed away from mid-grey, 0.5 flattens it. Pivot stays at 0.5.",
        "delay-trigger": "Clock.quarter → in, out → Envelope.trigger: a second swell lands DELAY seconds after each beat — call-and-response choreography.",
        "depth-drive": "Depth.depth → Depth Drive.depth, Depth Drive.z → Output.z: near surfaces lift toward the camera. GAIN sets travel, GAMMA bends the response curve.",
        "depth-fog": "Video Color.color → color, Depth.depth → depth, color → Output.color: far pins sink into the FOGR/FOGG/FOGB color; DENSITY sets how thick the haze is.",
        "depth-gradient": "Depth.depth → t, color → Output.color: near pins take the NEARR/NEARG/NEARB color, far pins the FARR/FARG/FARB color — a hand-picked two-stop ramp.",
        "displace": "Scatter.offset → Displace.offset, Displace.out → Output.position: one AMOUNT knob (0-4) scales the whole motion — expose AMOUNT and drive it from Hand Pinch.distance.",
        "divide": "Depth.depth → a, Constant.out (VALUE 2) → b; out → Output.z halves the push. Divisors are kept away from 0 (sign preserved), so b = 0 reads as a tiny positive.",
        "duotone": "Video Color.color → color, color → Output.color: dark pins take the SHADOWR/G/B color, bright pins the LIGHTR/G/B color — instant risograph.",
        "echo": "Depth.z → Echo.in, Echo.out → Output.z: a soft ghost surface chases live motion by ~DELAY seconds; FEEDBACK regenerates the tail.",
        "fft-band": "Pick BAND (1 ≈ 40 Hz sub → 20 ≈ 8 kHz); level → Size.size follows just that slice of the music. Stack several nodes on different bands for a spectrum-split patch.",
        "field-curve": "Depth.depth → in, CURVE 2; out → Palette.t eases the gradient so colour piles up on the nearest pins.",
        "field-fold": "Depth.depth → in, PIVOT 0.5 GAIN 2; out → Size.size — mid-depth pins shrink to nothing, near and far pins grow: a centre-out V.",
        "fract": "Transport.time → in; out → Palette.t loops the colormap once per second — sawtooth wrap for any growing value.",
        "grain": "Add it, AMOUNT 0.15-0.3: animated film texture over the final frame (also on NDI/Record output). 1.0 = full VHS.",
        "hand-openness": "Wire amount → Shape Morph.blend (TARGET cube): a slow fist→palm sweeps spheres into cubes continuously. SMOOTHING 0.3 steadies Vision jitter.",
        "head-pose": "Expose SHIFT on Hue Shift and wire x → Hue Shift.shift: walking across frame sweeps the cloud's hue; SMOOTHING 0.5 steadies head jitter.",
        "hide": "Ellipse Region.mask → Hide.mask, Hide.size → Size.size: pins outside the circle vanish. MODE=cutoff snaps hard at THRESHOLD; INVERT flips inside/out.",
        "hsv-shift": "Palette.color → color, out → Output.color; SHIFT 0.17 rotates every hue a sixth of the color wheel — detune any map live.",
        "joint": "Pick JOINT (leftAnkle, rightShoulder…); x/y drive anything like Hand Position does, speed → Size.size lights you up when that joint moves. Slew after it for extra glide.",
        "lag": "Depth.z → Lag.in, Lag.out → Output.z: the surface catches up to live depth over HALFLIFE seconds — dreamy motion smear. HALFLIFE 0 = off.",
        "left-hand-gesture": "Wire palm → Counter.count: each left-palm show steps the counter; expose SHIFT on Palette and Counter.value → Palette.shift steps the colors.",
        "left-hand-pinch": "Set OUTMAX 1, expose FOCUS on Depth, wire distance → Depth.focus: a closed left pinch stills the cloud, spreading adds sensor life.",
        "light-gradient": "Video Color.color → color, color → Output.color: bright camera areas climb the MAP colormap; INTENSITY scales what counts as bright.",
        "live-update": "Wire Hand Gesture.palm/fist/peace/point → in1–in4: the card names whichever is active ('FIST'); HOLD bridges brief dropouts; out carries the active input's index.",
        "look-at": "Add it with Shape TYPE = slab or spike: every pin turns to face the X/Y/Z point. Expose X/Y and wire Hand Position — the whole cloud tracks your hand like iron filings.",
        "macro": "Select several nodes, hit GROUP in the bar: they collapse into one card (wires keep flowing, dragging moves the whole group). EXPAND or delete the card to spread them back out.",
        "material": "SHADING = unlit for flat poster color, matcap for a studio look, lit + low ROUGHNESS for glossy highlights (add a Light and drag it around). METALLIC tints the shine with the pin's own color.",
        "max": "Depth.depth → a, Ripple.height → b; out → Output.z lets ripples only ever raise the surface, never dig into it.",
        "midi-cc": "value → Size.size, then turn any knob on a USB or network (RTP) MIDI controller. Every CC number lands on this one node — last received wins.",
        "midi-note": "gate → Envelope.trigger and velocity → Size.size: hold any key to swell the cloud, hit harder for bigger pins.",
        "min": "Depth.depth → a, Wave.height → b; out → Output.z — each pin takes the lower surface, like water clipping through a body.",
        "mix": "Depth.depth → a, Noise.out → b; out → Output.z. T 0.5 sits halfway; expose T and wire LFO.out into its port to crossfade the two surfaces.",
        "multiply": "Size.out → a, LFO.out → b; out → Output.size pulses every pin with the LFO — the universal 'apply amount' node.",
